WEBVTT

00:02.609 --> 00:04.542
Oh, the... there's
a 7:15 at the ArcLight.

00:04.962 --> 00:06.506
Well, that doesn't give
us much time to eat.

00:06.530 --> 00:07.696
We can eat afterwards.

00:07.765 --> 00:09.632
I'm not gonna eat
at 10:00 at night.

00:09.700 --> 00:11.000
Who am I, Hemingway?

00:12.603 --> 00:14.770
Why do you think
Hemingway ate at 10:00?

00:14.839 --> 00:17.006
He spent a lot of time in
Spain. They eat dinner late.

00:17.074 --> 00:18.841
He also spent
a lot of time in Florida.

00:18.909 --> 00:20.454
Last time I was there,
people were eating dinner

00:20.478 --> 00:22.344
at, like, 4:30.

00:22.413 --> 00:23.679
You guys know

00:23.748 --> 00:26.448
that Hemingway had
cats with six toes?

00:27.585 --> 00:30.686
Six toes per foot
or six toes total?

00:30.755 --> 00:32.154
Okay.

00:32.223 --> 00:34.303
It's official. We're never
going to see the <i>Avengers.</i>

00:34.959 --> 00:36.892
Guys, just come on.
Make a decision.

00:36.961 --> 00:38.494
I-I'm good with
eating after.

00:38.562 --> 00:41.063
- Mm, I'm kind of hungry now.
- Yeah, me, too.

00:41.132 --> 00:42.576
- Then we'll eat before.
- Okay.

00:42.600 --> 00:45.534
So, then, we can see the 3-D
at 9:00 or the 2-D at 9:30.

00:45.603 --> 00:47.202
3-D.
If I'm gonna see Thor,

00:47.271 --> 00:49.872
I want to feel like
I could lick those abs.

00:51.208 --> 00:53.342
Actually,
3-D kind of makes me queasy.

00:53.411 --> 00:54.810
No, but we have to see it
in 3-D.

00:54.879 --> 00:57.079
We saw part one in 3-D,
and the 2-D part two

00:57.148 --> 00:59.148
is not the part two
of the 3-D part one.

01:00.618 --> 01:02.451
He's got you there, Leonard.
Or he doesn't.

01:02.520 --> 01:04.352
I don't really care anymore.

01:04.422 --> 01:05.486
Okay, then,

01:05.556 --> 01:06.833
- we'll go see it in 3-D.
- No.

01:06.857 --> 01:08.869
Sweetie, you shouldn't do things
that make you feel bad.

01:08.893 --> 01:11.327
Well, I'm doing this.

01:11.395 --> 01:12.728
And of course he is.

01:12.797 --> 01:14.697
He is a textbook satisficer.

01:14.765 --> 01:16.098
That's not even a word.

01:16.167 --> 01:17.333
Uh, yes, it is.

01:17.368 --> 01:19.768
According to Nobel Prize-winning
economist Herbert Simon,

01:19.837 --> 01:21.770
satisficing is a
decision-making strategy

01:21.839 --> 01:23.238
whereby a person accepts

01:23.307 --> 01:25.674
whatever available
option is satisfactory

01:25.743 --> 01:27.187
rather than seeking out
a course of action

01:27.211 --> 01:28.477
that would make him happiest,

01:28.546 --> 01:31.013
as I just did when I explained
what satisficing was.

01:32.083 --> 01:33.315
He's right.

01:33.351 --> 01:34.650
No one wanted to hear at.

01:34.719 --> 01:36.418
He knew it, yet
he plowed ahead.

01:37.655 --> 01:39.455
I'm just trying to find a plan

01:39.523 --> 01:40.756
that makes everyone happy.

01:40.825 --> 01:42.024
Except you.

01:42.093 --> 01:44.026
Yeah, Leonard.
What would make you happy?

01:44.095 --> 01:46.228
I could tell you about
satisficing again.

01:46.297 --> 01:47.507
You know,
what would make me happy

01:47.531 --> 01:49.098
is if we just stop talking
about this

01:49.166 --> 01:50.477
and see whatever movie
you guys want to see

01:50.501 --> 01:51.611
whenever you want to see it.

01:51.635 --> 01:53.438
Okay. But next time,
we get to pick.

