03:04.967 --> 03:06.277
I mean, come on,
when was the last time

03:06.301 --> 03:07.979
you did something
totally selfish without worrying

03:08.003 --> 03:09.147
about what anyone else wanted?

03:09.171 --> 03:10.270
Uh...

03:10.339 --> 03:11.604
according to my mother,

03:11.673 --> 03:13.840
I took my sweet time being born.

03:16.912 --> 03:18.645
How is that selfish?

03:18.714 --> 03:21.915
Apparently, she had
dinner reservations.

03:24.553 --> 03:26.519
And this is the telescope room

03:26.588 --> 03:28.955
where I spend a lot
of my evenings.

03:29.024 --> 03:30.690
Where's the telescope?

03:30.759 --> 03:32.425
Hawaii.

03:32.494 --> 03:33.760
That's cool.

03:33.829 --> 03:35.595
Yeah, so, you know...

03:35.664 --> 03:37.097
aloha.

03:40.002 --> 03:42.068
What's that smell?

03:42.137 --> 03:44.204
Uh, everyone has
their own theory.

03:44.272 --> 03:45.805
Dr. Tibourgh thinks it's mold.

03:45.874 --> 03:47.674
I think it's Dr. Tibourgh.

03:49.044 --> 03:50.977
So, what am I looking at?

03:51.046 --> 03:53.413
Ah, this is live information

03:53.482 --> 03:55.415
from the Keck telescope.
It's pretty interesting.

03:55.484 --> 03:58.318
So, I recently observed
some optical flashes.

03:58.387 --> 04:00.587
It could be light bouncing
off a natural object,

04:00.655 --> 04:01.866
but those tend to
be less reflective,

04:01.890 --> 04:03.857
so could be evidence of
something alien-made.

04:04.960 --> 04:07.093
Oh, this suddenly got exciting.

04:07.162 --> 04:08.895
Oh. When you say "exciting,"

04:08.964 --> 04:10.508
do you mean "go back
to my place" exciting

04:10.532 --> 04:12.165
or "hold our breath
and do it here"?

04:15.771 --> 04:17.704
Mahalo.

04:25.247 --> 04:27.180
Do I want to ask?

04:28.250 --> 04:30.183
Oh, w... when I go upstairs,

04:30.252 --> 04:32.585
Penny's gonna make me choose
what we're gonna do tonight

04:32.654 --> 04:34.587
without taking her feelings
into consideration,

04:34.656 --> 04:36.589
and I-I don't know
if I'm up for it.

04:38.593 --> 04:40.527
Poor baby.
When I go upstairs,

04:40.595 --> 04:42.429
Sheldon's gonna give me
a 25-minute lecture

04:42.497 --> 04:45.532
about what Hulk would be like
if he were made of metal.

04:46.902 --> 04:48.234
Part of his ongoing series,

04:48.303 --> 04:51.304
"What If Hulk Were Made
of Other Things?"

04:51.373 --> 04:54.107
I-I've always been
a people pleaser.

04:54.176 --> 04:56.643
Is that so bad?
It's gotten me this far.

04:56.711 --> 04:59.379
What, almost up four
flights of stairs?

05:00.449 --> 05:02.449
Okay, if I go in there

05:02.517 --> 05:05.285
and pick something I want to do
that she also wants to do,

05:05.353 --> 05:07.165
she's gonna think I'm just
picking it to make her happy.

05:07.189 --> 05:08.688
So I feel like

05:08.757 --> 05:10.868
I have to pick something
I know she doesn't want to do

05:10.892 --> 05:12.132
or she's gonna be disappointed.

05:12.160 --> 05:13.493
Right?
What do you think?

05:13.562 --> 05:15.795
Think I've got ice cream
in this bag

05:15.864 --> 05:17.130
that's starting to melt.

05:18.233 --> 05:19.432
I'm sorry.

05:19.501 --> 05:21.868
It's exhausting
being in my head.

05:21.937 --> 05:24.504
Look, when you wanted
Penny, you didn't care

05:24.573 --> 05:26.940
what anybody else
thought or wanted,

05:27.008 --> 05:28.341
including Penny.

05:30.412 --> 05:32.679
That's true.

05:32.747 --> 05:34.948
Yeah, yeah,
there was something I wanted,

05:35.016 --> 05:37.684
I went after it and I got it.

05:37.752 --> 05:40.192
Now you're hiding from it on the
stairs, so it all worked out.

05:42.958 --> 05:44.457
Hey.

05:44.526 --> 05:45.937
I thought about what
I want to do tonight,

05:45.961 --> 05:48.728
and I didn't take your feelings
into consideration at all.

05:49.798 --> 05:51.197
Great.

05:51.266 --> 05:52.732
I want to have sex.

05:53.802 --> 05:56.336
Wow, sex with your wife.

05:56.404 --> 05:59.539
You're really swinging for
the fences there, Hofstadter.

05:59.608 --> 06:01.274
Yeah, we don't have to.

06:01.343 --> 06:02.475
No!

06:02.544 --> 06:03.810
I like it.
Let's go.

06:03.879 --> 06:05.278
Oh, o-okay.

06:05.347 --> 06:06.757
And then after that,
we're gonna watch

06:06.781 --> 06:08.114
<i>Star Trek: Discovery.</i>
- All right.

06:08.183 --> 06:10.950
Well, just a warning, I might be
on my phone for most of it.

06:11.019 --> 06:12.752
That's fine.

06:12.821 --> 06:14.165
Wait, you mean
just the <i>Star Trek...</i>

06:14.189 --> 06:16.222
Actually, I don't care.

06:18.627 --> 06:21.027
And, with apologies
to Lady Gaga,

06:21.096 --> 06:23.563
that's how a star is born.

06:25.467 --> 06:28.168
Told you he was
gonna mention Lady Gaga.

06:29.671 --> 06:31.511
At least he didn't talk
about how much he cried

06:31.573 --> 06:32.805
during that movie.

06:32.874 --> 06:34.140
Although,

06:34.209 --> 06:35.820
if you haven't seen that movie,
you should.

06:35.844 --> 06:37.744
I cried so much.

06:39.481 --> 06:41.214
Well, that's the lecture
for today.

06:41.283 --> 06:43.116
Uh, let's open it up
for questions.

06:43.185 --> 06:45.385
Uh...

06:46.288 --> 06:47.787
Oh, you! Sir, yes.

06:47.856 --> 06:48.922
You have a question?

06:48.990 --> 06:51.791
Yeah. Actually,
I have a two-part question.

06:51.860 --> 06:54.627
Are you sure? I get the sense
it's only one part.

06:55.697 --> 06:57.263
No, no, it's two.

06:57.332 --> 06:59.232
Part one: the new star

06:59.301 --> 07:00.366
you were talking about--

07:00.435 --> 07:02.602
how long did it take
that light to reach Earth?

07:02.671 --> 07:03.970
And part two:

07:04.039 --> 07:05.516
is it true you plant
your friends in the audience

07:05.540 --> 07:07.607
to ask questions?

07:07.676 --> 07:09.609
46,000 years.

07:09.678 --> 07:11.044
And no,
I don't plant my friends,

07:11.112 --> 07:13.479
because apparently,
I don't have any.

07:15.250 --> 07:16.616
Uh, any other questions?

07:16.685 --> 07:19.152
- Uh, yes. You, miss.
- Hi.

07:19.221 --> 07:21.521
I read your paper on specular
reflections. It was great.

07:21.590 --> 07:23.390
- Oh, thank you so much.
- In your conclusion,

07:23.425 --> 07:25.792
you said you couldn't rule out
that light flashes

07:25.860 --> 07:28.027
could be evidence
of alien civilization.

07:28.096 --> 07:31.130
So does that mean
you think it's aliens?

07:31.166 --> 07:33.399
I was just illustrating
that there are many unknowns,

07:33.468 --> 07:34.867
and as scientists, we can't

07:34.936 --> 07:36.736
preemptively rule out
possibilities.

07:36.805 --> 07:38.838
So you think it's aliens.

07:38.907 --> 07:41.107
- A-Actually, no, that's...
- I have a question

07:41.176 --> 07:43.276
about the aliens you found.

07:43.345 --> 07:45.645
That's not what I said, Howard.

07:45.714 --> 07:47.313
Hold on a second.

07:47.382 --> 07:50.216
Do you two know each other?

07:50.285 --> 07:51.651
Yeah.

07:51.720 --> 07:52.852
My sister was--

07:52.921 --> 07:55.888
a-and this is her term--
abducted.

07:57.492 --> 08:00.560
Do you think those could be
the same aliens...

08:00.629 --> 08:03.062
Okay, any other questions? Mm.

08:03.131 --> 08:04.163
Not about aliens?

08:06.101 --> 08:07.300
What?

08:07.369 --> 08:09.213
Do you still want me to
ask the one you gave me?

08:09.237 --> 08:11.671
'Cause it kind of feels
like we're past that.

08:14.476 --> 08:16.542
Ooh, Leonard,
I don't mean to alarm you,

08:16.611 --> 08:19.045
but the Chinese food
smells funny.

08:19.114 --> 08:20.780
That's because it's barbecue.

08:21.850 --> 08:24.417
But it's Chinese food night.

08:24.486 --> 08:25.930
Um, I picked it. You're
the one who told me

08:25.954 --> 08:28.087
to stop being such a
satisficer all the time.

08:28.156 --> 08:29.589
What?
I did not.

08:29.658 --> 08:31.424
I just pointed out
that you were one.

08:31.493 --> 08:33.693
It's what I like best about you.

08:33.761 --> 08:36.696
Well, that and those little
notes you leave in my lunch.

08:38.099 --> 08:40.033
I leave those!

08:41.469 --> 08:43.068
Well, that's disappointing.

08:43.138 --> 08:44.148
I already know
that you heart me.

08:44.172 --> 08:46.472
Now I don't know
if Leonard does.

08:46.541 --> 08:48.308
Well, this is what
we're having for dinner.

08:48.376 --> 08:50.510
You can eat it or not.
I don't care.

08:50.578 --> 08:52.612
I guess that answers
the heart question.

08:52.681 --> 08:55.148
I-It's fine.
We'll have barbecue.

08:55.216 --> 08:57.784
Oh, of course.
I'm nothing if not flexible.

08:57.852 --> 08:59.852
I'm sure that at some point

08:59.921 --> 09:02.288
in the 3,000-year history
of the Chinese empire,

09:02.357 --> 09:04.190
a cavalryman crossing

09:04.259 --> 09:07.126
the Gobi Desert was forced
by hunger to eat his own horse

09:07.195 --> 09:08.272
and roast it over a campfire,

09:08.296 --> 09:10.496
hence, Chinese barbecue.
Let's eat.

09:12.600 --> 09:15.535
Gee, I'm sorry, I didn't
watch the news today.

09:15.603 --> 09:18.104
Has the whole world gone mad?

09:18.173 --> 09:19.839
It's my house.

09:19.908 --> 09:22.709
I'm tired of being told
where I can and can't sit.

09:24.446 --> 09:26.746
You did this.

09:26.815 --> 09:28.715
Amy, grab your meat.
We're leaving in a huff.

09:31.653 --> 09:33.720
I'm sorry, if I don't go now,
it's not a huff.

09:36.925 --> 09:39.025
Don't take this the wrong way,

09:39.094 --> 09:41.494
but that was even more exciting
than the sex.

