10:11.129 --> 10:13.229
and he finds
the new you tiresome.

10:14.800 --> 10:16.733
How is that different
than the old you?

10:16.802 --> 10:18.835
The new me gives knowing winks.

10:21.873 --> 10:23.273
Well, all these years,

10:23.341 --> 10:25.608
I-I was afraid to say
what I wanted.

10:25.677 --> 10:27.210
You know, even at work,

10:27.279 --> 10:29.079
you know, there's things
I want to accomplish,

10:29.114 --> 10:32.215
but I didn't want to ruffle any
feathers or step on any toes.

10:32.284 --> 10:34.217
Feathers and toes?
Is the new thing you're trying

10:34.286 --> 10:36.953
to accomplish ballroom dancing
with a chicken?

10:37.022 --> 10:40.023
Look at that--
the new me is hilarious.

10:40.091 --> 10:42.492
Always wanted to be
the principal investigator

10:42.561 --> 10:44.761
on a plasma physics study.

10:44.830 --> 10:47.597
Hey, look at that--
the new you's funny, too.

10:48.700 --> 10:50.900
I'm serious.
You know...

10:50.969 --> 10:52.469
I'm gonna put together
a proposal

10:52.537 --> 10:54.617
and tell President Siebert
this is what I want to do.

10:54.673 --> 10:55.839
If he doesn't let me,

10:55.907 --> 10:57.941
there's plenty of other
universities that will.

10:58.009 --> 10:59.709
Sure there are.

11:02.013 --> 11:03.947
Of course you don't
want me to do that,

11:04.015 --> 11:05.577
because you like it when
you're successful and I'm not.

11:05.578 --> 11:07.784
No, you're confusing
causation and...

11:07.853 --> 11:10.520
"Welcome to Alhambra."
Where the heck are we?

11:13.258 --> 11:15.391
Now I'm some sort
of big joke.

11:15.460 --> 11:18.094
I'm even on some
alien conspiracy blog.

11:18.129 --> 11:20.196
See? "Caltech
astrophysicist

11:20.265 --> 11:22.365
finds proof of alien life''

11:23.935 --> 11:26.202
Wow, that is not
a great picture of you.

11:26.271 --> 11:27.770
That's not the point.

11:27.839 --> 11:29.138
Dr. Koothrappali.

11:29.207 --> 11:31.741
I'm surprised to see you in here.
Why is that?

11:31.810 --> 11:32.976
Because the truth...

11:33.044 --> 11:34.978
is out there!

11:37.282 --> 11:39.449
You see? That's what
I'm talking about.

11:39.518 --> 11:41.451
People have been doing
that to me all day.

11:41.520 --> 11:43.286
Relax.
They're just having fun.

11:45.790 --> 11:47.724
Oh, come on!

11:50.161 --> 11:51.161
See? It's fun.

11:58.870 --> 12:00.370
Wow. Déjà vu.

12:01.473 --> 12:03.106
Amy, you're a neuroscientist--

12:03.174 --> 12:05.308
you know the latest research
into déjà vu suggests

12:05.377 --> 12:07.610
it's nothing but
the frontal regions of the brain

12:07.679 --> 12:09.712
attempting to correct
an inaccurate memory.

12:09.781 --> 12:11.748
You telling me stuff
I already know

12:11.816 --> 12:13.483
is definitely déjà vu.

12:14.753 --> 12:16.953
How about telling me
something I don't know,

12:17.022 --> 12:19.689
like why you're
sitting on the stairs.

12:19.758 --> 12:22.659
How can I tell if I'm doing
something for a noble reason

12:22.727 --> 12:24.160
or a selfish reason?

12:25.297 --> 12:27.330
Try saying the thing
in your head

12:27.399 --> 12:30.867
and see if you can add
the words, "That'll show 'em."

12:32.437 --> 12:34.370
Leonard's about to demand a job

12:34.439 --> 12:37.040
that I don't think
the university will give him.

12:37.108 --> 12:39.242
I'm worried he's making
a giant mistake.

12:39.311 --> 12:41.244
But maybe I only
think that because

12:41.313 --> 12:44.113
deep down I don't
want him to succeed.

12:45.517 --> 12:48.017
The fact that you're worried
about your motivation

12:48.086 --> 12:51.521
supports the idea that you
genuinely care for your friend.

12:53.925 --> 12:56.192
I do.

12:56.261 --> 12:57.927
Thank you, Amy.

12:57.996 --> 12:59.128
You know what?

12:59.197 --> 13:00.797
After I've talked to Leonard,

13:00.865 --> 13:03.466
you've earned yourself
a bonus lecture on Sponge Hulk.

13:07.072 --> 13:08.271
That'll show me.

13:12.310 --> 13:15.011
So, I spent the whole day
putting together this proposal,

13:15.080 --> 13:17.246
and tomorrow I'm gonna
tell President Siebert

13:17.315 --> 13:19.415
that this is what
I want to do.

13:19.484 --> 13:22.085
Oh. Well, this...

13:22.153 --> 13:24.787
looks great.

13:24.856 --> 13:27.156
- You didn't even open it.
- Well, no,

13:27.225 --> 13:28.391
it's got a nice, you know,

13:28.460 --> 13:30.727
science-y heft to it. I...

13:30.795 --> 13:32.428
Really proud of
you, sweetie.

13:33.598 --> 13:34.797
Leonard?

13:34.866 --> 13:36.199
- Hmm?
- Um,

13:36.267 --> 13:37.867
I have been agonizing

13:37.936 --> 13:40.036
over whether or not
to say something to you.

13:40.105 --> 13:41.971
Aw. Let me help. Don't.

13:43.074 --> 13:44.407
I have to.

13:44.476 --> 13:47.510
I don't think that you
should demand to be in charge

13:47.579 --> 13:48.911
of a plasma project.

13:48.980 --> 13:50.079
Well, big surprise.

13:50.148 --> 13:52.849
You can't stand the idea
of me succeeding.

13:52.917 --> 13:54.350
No. I'll be honest.

13:54.419 --> 13:57.387
New assertive Leonard is going
to take some getting used to.

13:57.455 --> 14:00.123
But so did
cargo pants Leonard, hmm?

14:00.191 --> 14:02.091
Who, for the record,
I miss.

14:02.160 --> 14:04.727
He always had gum.

14:04.796 --> 14:07.096
Sheldon, if this is what he
wants, he should ask for it.

14:07.165 --> 14:09.198
I mean, what's the worst
that happens? They say no.

14:09.267 --> 14:10.933
Well, I'm not
gonna let them say no.

14:11.002 --> 14:13.970
If they don't want me to quit,
this is what it's gonna take.

14:14.039 --> 14:15.538
Wait, you're gonna quit?

14:15.607 --> 14:18.174
Yeah. It's like you said,
I have to go after what I want,

14:18.243 --> 14:19.876
and if I can't get that
at Caltech,

14:19.944 --> 14:21.984
there are plenty of other
universities in the world.

14:22.047 --> 14:23.546
W... In the world?

14:23.615 --> 14:25.415
I can't even get you
to go to the beach,

14:25.450 --> 14:28.184
and now you want to
move to the world?

14:28.253 --> 14:30.357
Well, I don't want to, but
if that's what I have to do...

14:30.381 --> 14:31.288
Okay, don't you think

14:31.289 --> 14:32.633
threatening to quit
your job is something

14:32.657 --> 14:34.023
you should run by me first?

14:34.092 --> 14:36.259
You said I shouldn't
worry about your feelings.

14:36.327 --> 14:39.028
I meant feelings about things
that I don't care about!

14:39.097 --> 14:40.841
Now, I'm not quite sure
when to jump in here...

14:40.865 --> 14:42.732
- Not now.
- Okay.

14:42.801 --> 14:45.168
Fine, you want to talk about it?
Let's talk about it.

14:45.236 --> 14:47.170
I-I'm not loving
my job right now.

14:47.238 --> 14:49.119
And this is something
that would make me happy.

14:49.297 --> 14:50.351
Don't you want me to be happy?

14:50.375 --> 14:52.076
Oh, I've been dinged
on this before.

14:52.077 --> 14:54.811
Whatever you really think,
you have to say yes.

14:54.879 --> 14:58.281
- Of course I want you to be happy.
- Well played.

14:58.349 --> 15:01.084
Okay, I know this seems scary,

15:01.152 --> 15:03.453
but I put together
a strong proposal.

15:03.521 --> 15:05.855
It's good for me,
it's good for the university.

15:05.924 --> 15:07.757
They're gonna give it to me.

15:07.826 --> 15:09.092
No.

15:10.829 --> 15:12.361
I'm sorry, President Siebert,

15:12.430 --> 15:14.597
but I'm not taking no
for an answer.

15:14.666 --> 15:16.265
I speak a little Russian.

15:16.334 --> 15:18.868
Will you take <i>nyet</i>
for an answer?

15:18.937 --> 15:20.670
I'm serious.

15:20.739 --> 15:22.872
Oh.
Well, that changes everything.

15:22.941 --> 15:24.874
- Really?
- <i>Nyet.</i>

15:27.812 --> 15:30.113
I know a lot of people
have been having fun

15:30.181 --> 15:32.315
claiming that I said
I found alien life.

15:32.383 --> 15:33.783
I want to make it clear

15:33.852 --> 15:36.519
that is not what I said.

15:36.588 --> 15:38.921
I did say that was
one possible explanation.

15:38.990 --> 15:40.923
I don't think
that's something to mock.

15:40.992 --> 15:43.459
Right? It would be arrogant
for us to assume

15:43.528 --> 15:45.728
that we are alone
in the universe.

15:45.797 --> 15:47.897
And as scientists,
we need to remain open

15:47.966 --> 15:50.733
to the possibility
that the truth may sound silly

15:50.802 --> 15:52.168
or far-fetched.

15:52.237 --> 15:55.071
Uh, the round Earth.
Germs that cause diseases.

15:55.140 --> 15:56.405
Subatomic particles.

15:56.474 --> 15:58.407
All these at one time
seemed fanciful.

15:58.476 --> 16:00.743
So who's to say
what science fiction of today

16:00.812 --> 16:02.645
will be the reality of tomorrow?

16:03.748 --> 16:06.082
Will there be colonies on Mars?

16:06.151 --> 16:08.184
Uh, matter transporters?

16:08.253 --> 16:10.686
Perhaps the Loch Ness Monster
is real.

16:10.755 --> 16:13.322
Who knows?
I'm just saying that...

16:13.391 --> 16:15.825
the only way
science moves forward

16:15.894 --> 16:18.494
is to follow the evidence
wherever it leads,

16:18.563 --> 16:21.364
even if it makes us
sound crazy sometimes.

16:21.432 --> 16:23.099
Hey, Bernie,
look at this.

16:23.168 --> 16:25.935
"Caltech astrophysicist claims

16:26.004 --> 16:28.971
Loch Ness Monster is real."

16:33.778 --> 16:35.611
- Hey. How did it go?
- Great.

16:35.680 --> 16:36.946
What, so you got the job?

16:37.015 --> 16:39.048
I did not.

16:39.117 --> 16:41.284
So you quit?
Okay, Leonard, I can't move.

16:41.352 --> 16:44.187
I just bought a six-month
membership to SoulCycle.

16:45.290 --> 16:47.323
Well, I-I didn't quit.

16:47.392 --> 16:48.658
I said I was going to.

16:48.726 --> 16:51.093
I walked out the door
and started crying.

16:51.162 --> 16:54.697
You know, "Oh, my, God, oh, my
God, oh, my God, what'd I do?"

16:54.766 --> 16:57.033
And then he called me back in.

16:57.101 --> 16:58.668
Then he changed his mind?

16:58.736 --> 16:59.802
He did not.

16:59.871 --> 17:01.804
I'm really confused about

17:01.873 --> 17:03.773
how to react to this story.

17:05.042 --> 17:07.343
President Siebert
didn't want to lose me.

17:07.412 --> 17:08.877
Even though
they couldn't make me

17:08.946 --> 17:11.247
a lead investigator
on a plasma team,

17:11.316 --> 17:13.249
there was an opening
for a co-lead

17:13.318 --> 17:14.851
on a photon entanglement team.

17:14.919 --> 17:16.117
How cool is that?

17:16.186 --> 17:19.055
You're gonna have to tell me.

17:20.157 --> 17:21.624
It's really cool.

17:21.693 --> 17:24.093
Yay! Oh, I am so
happy for you.

17:24.162 --> 17:27.597
I almost got what I wanted,
and it never would have happened

17:27.665 --> 17:29.966
if you hadn't almost believed in me.
- Oh.

17:31.202 --> 17:33.102
Let's celebrate.
What do you want to do?

17:33.171 --> 17:35.872
Oh, please don't make me
decide another thing.

17:35.940 --> 17:37.540
Hey, you want to go
to SoulCycle with me?

17:37.575 --> 17:39.809
Give me a minute,
I'll think of something.

17:45.530 --> 17:47.170
Now, I know what
You're you're thinking:

17:47.198 --> 17:50.866
isn't Broccoli Hulk basically
just the Jolly Green Giant?

17:51.936 --> 17:53.903
That <i>is</i> what I was thinking.

17:53.971 --> 17:56.272
Let's never discuss it again.

17:57.375 --> 17:58.441
Really?

17:59.677 --> 18:01.944
- Are you hiding from Penny again?
- No. No, no, no.

18:02.013 --> 18:05.481
I-I went to SoulCycle with her,
and my legs hurt so bad, I...

18:05.550 --> 18:08.084
literally can't stand up.

18:08.152 --> 18:10.719
Sheldon, why don't you
keep him company.

18:12.490 --> 18:13.923
All right.

18:16.160 --> 18:17.927
Hello, Leonard.
Hey.

18:22.733 --> 18:24.600
Have you ever wondered

18:24.669 --> 18:28.137
what the Hulk would be like
if he were made of sherbet?

18:31.142 --> 18:32.708
I give up.

18:33.811 --> 18:35.444
Delicious.

